          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Make no mistake: Sh=
ould this movement succeed, it will be an earthquake in the House Democrati=
c caucus. Both parties in both chambers prize seniority when it comes to co=
mmittee leadership=E2=80=94but it=E2=80=99s <i>especially</i> imperative am=
ong House Democrats, who, unlike their Republican colleagues, don=E2=80=99t=
 have strict term limits for committee leaders. Democrats can wait two or t=
hree decades for an opening=E2=80=94often not assuming committee leadership=
 until their 70s=E2=80=94and don=E2=80=99t give up the perch easily. <br/><=
br/>Upending this precedent would radically change the way the House Democr=
atic caucus functions. There=E2=80=99s a reason it=E2=80=99s never been don=
e before: The undisputed power center of the House Democrats, the Congressi=
onal Black Caucus, generally prioritizes seniority for such posts. (The C.B=
=2EC. has upheld this principle even to the point of defying
<b>Nancy Pelosi</b> in the trench warfare of <u><a href=3D"https://email.pu=
ck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUaFAxVldmd04xbHZiWFI=
0elVVbz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9yb2xsY2FsbC5jb20vMjAxNC8xMS8xOS9wYWxsb25lLW=
